children.subject: +1, a summer class will go roughly twice the pace of one during the semester. 162 is already a fast-paced, intense class -- at the increased pace, doing that plus any other class seems like an incredibly punishing workload.
162 and 186 together over the summer would be brutal (assuming the summer classes cover all the content covered during regular semesters).
Wait, is 186 being offered over the summer? I can't seem to find it on summer.berkeley.edu.

history.content: Since the registration for summer classes is going to open up in a few weeks, I was wondering if anyone could give me some advice about talking CS 162 and CS 186 over the summer? And I was wondering if anyone could give me some advice about what it would be like taking CS 161, 168, and 170 during Fall. I know I want to take those five classes over summer and fall, and I'm wondering what the best combination would be to not fry my brain too badly. Thank you.
